---
import Layout from "../components/layouts/LayoutLegal.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <div id="policygen-privacy-policy" class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <h1 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Last updated March 5, 2026</h3>

    <!-- Privacy notice -->
    <section class="mb-8">
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        This privacy policy ("Policy") for Rothco Built, LLC ("we", "us", "our") describes how we
        collect, protect and use the personally identifiable information ("Personal Information")
        you ("user", "you" or "your") provide on <a
          href="https://rothcollc.com"
          class="text-blue-500 hover:underline">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;rothcollc.com</a
        > and any of its products or services (collectively, "Website" or "Services") such as
      </p>
      <ul class="mb-4 list-disc pl-5">
        <li>
          Visit our website at <a href="https://rothcollc.com" class="text-blue-500 hover:underline"
            >https:&#x2F;&#x2F;rothcollc.com</a
          > or use any website that is part of our network.
        </li>

        <li>
          Use any of our other products or services, engage with our sales, marketing or any virtual
          or real world events that are part of our network.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        Please read this privacy policy carefully, it contains important information about your
        rights and how we handle your personal information. If you disagree or have concerns about
        our privacy policy, please do not use our website or services or contact us at <a
          href="mailto:scott@rothcollc.com"
          class="text-blue-500 hover:underline">scott@rothcollc.com</a
        >.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Summary -->
    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">Summary (TL;DR)</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        This summary section is provided for your convenience. To read the full privacy policy,
        scroll down or click on any of the linked sections.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        <span class="font-bold">What personal information do we collect and process?</span>

        We may collect and process personal information from you as you visit and use our website.
        You can find more information about the
        <a href="#personal-information" class="text-blue-500 hover:underline"
          >personal information we collect</a
        >
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        <span class="font-bold">What sensitive information do we collect and process?</span>

        We do not collect or process any sensitive information from you.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        <span class="font-bold">Do we collect information from third parties?</span>

        We may collect information from third parties. You can find more information about the
        <a href="#third-party-data" class="text-blue-500 hover:underline"
          >third parties we collect information from</a
        >
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        <span class="font-bold">Do we share information with third parties?</span>

        We may share information with third parties. You can find more information about the
        <a href="#third-party-sharing" class="text-blue-500 hover:underline"
          >third parties we share information with</a
        >
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        <span class="font-bold">How do we process your information?</span>
        We process your information to provide you with the services you have requested or are interested
        in. We may also use your information for other purposes such as improving our services, communicating
        with you, security and compliance and law enforcement. All information is collected and processed
        for only valid legal reasons with your consent, which you can withdraw at any time.
        <a href="#processing" class="text-blue-500 hover:underline"
          >More information about how we process your information</a
        >
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        <span class="font-bold">How do we protect your information?</span>
        We implement security measures to maintain the safety of your personal information. We take reasonable
        precautions and follow industry best practices to make sure it is not inappropriately lost, misused,
        accessed, disclosed, altered or destroyed.
        <a href="#security" class="text-blue-500 hover:underline"
          >More information about how we protect your information</a
        >
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        <span class="font-bold">How can you manage your personal information?</span>

        You have the right to access, update or delete your personal information. You can also
        object to the processing of your personal information, ask us to restrict processing of your
        personal information or request portability of your personal information. If you would like
        to exercise any of these rights, please contact us at <a
          href="mailto:scott@rothcollc.com"
          class="text-blue-500 hover:underline">scott@rothcollc.com</a
        >.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Policy Sections -->
    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">Privacy Policy Sections</h2>
      <ol class="mb-4 list-decimal pl-5">
        <li>
          <a href="#section-collected-information" class="text-blue-500 hover:underline"
            >Information we collect</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="#section-use" class="text-blue-500 hover:underline"
            >How we use or process your information</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="#legal-basis" class="text-blue-500 hover:underline"
            >Legal basis for information collection and processing</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="#section-third-party-sharing" class="text-blue-500 hover:underline"
            >Information sharing and disclosure</a
          >
        </li>

        <li>
          <a href="#section-web-tracking" class="text-blue-500 hover:underline"
            >Web tracking and cookies</a
          >
        </li>

        <li>
          <a href="#section-cookie-consent" class="text-blue-500 hover:underline"
            >Cookie Policy and Consent</a
          >
        </li>

        <li>
          <a href="#section-security" class="text-blue-500 hover:underline"
            >How we protect your information</a
          >
        </li>

        <li>
          <a href="#section-data-retention" class="text-blue-500 hover:underline">Data retention</a>
        </li>

        <li>
          <a href="#section-data-breach" class="text-blue-500 hover:underline"
            >Data Breach Notification</a
          >
        </li>

        <li>
          <a href="#section-us-state-privacy-laws" class="text-blue-500 hover:underline"
            >US State Privacy Laws</a
          >
        </li>

        <li>
          <a href="#section-privacy-rights" class="text-blue-500 hover:underline"
            >Your privacy rights</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="#section-privacy-policy-changes" class="text-blue-500 hover:underline"
            >Changes to our privacy policy</a
          >
        </li>
        <li><a href="#section-contact" class="text-blue-500 hover:underline">Contact us</a></li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <!-- Collected Information -->
    <section id="section-collected-information" class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">Information we collect</h2>
      <!-- Disclosed -->
      <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Information you disclose to us</h3>
      <!-- Personal -->

      <p id="personal-information" class="mb-4 text-base">
        We collect personal information that you voluntarily disclose to us during your visit and
        use of our services, participate in sales or marketing events or contact us. Information may
        include
      </p>
      <ul class="mb-4 list-disc pl-5">
        <li>Name</li>

        <li>Email</li>

        <li>Phone numbers</li>

        <li>Address</li>

        <li>Password</li>

        <li>ipAddress</li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Sensitive -->

      <p class="mb-4 text-base">We do not collect or process any sensitive information from you.</p>

      <!-- Payment Data -->

      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        We may collect and process payment information from you when you purchase our products or
        services, including credit cards, bank accounts, billing addresses, and other billing
        information.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        We use third-party payment processors to assist us in processing your payment information
        securely. Such third-party processors&#39; use of your personal information is governed by
        their respective privacy policies.
      </p>
      <ul class="mb-4 list-disc pl-5">
        <li>
          <a href="https://stripe.com/privacy" class="text-blue-500 hover:underline"
            >https://stripe.com/privacy</a
          >
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Social Login -->

      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        We offer the ability to register using a third party social network such as Facebook, Google
        etc. If you use a social login we may collect profile and social data from your social
        account. This may include your name, email, profile picture.
      </p>

      <!-- Derived Collected -->

      <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Information derived from your use of our services</h3>
      <!-- App Usage Data -->

      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        We may collect and log app usage data such as the date and time the app on your device
        accesses our servers and what information and files have been downloaded to the app based on
        your device number, ip address or user account.
      </p>

      <!-- Web Tracking -->

      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        We may use cookies to collect information about you and your activity across our website.
        Cookies are small data files stored on your device that help us improve our services and
        your experience.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">privacy_policy.information_we_collect.derived.web_tracking</p>

      <!-- Third Party -->

      <h3 id="third-party-data" class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">
        Information from third parties
      </h3>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        We may collect information about you from third parties such as marketing partners,
        affiliates, and other sources we may use to update our records, identify new customers or
        prevent fraud. Examples of information we receive from other sources include
      </p>
      <ul class="mb-4 list-disc pl-5">
        <li>analytics</li>

        <li>email</li>

        <li>support</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Use of Information -->
    <section id="section-use" class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">How we use or process your information</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        We use and process the information we collect for day to day running of our services, to
        improve our services, to communicate with you, to provide support, to protect our services,
        to comply with legal obligations and to enforce our terms and conditions.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4 text-base">Specific uses of information include</p>
      <ul class="mb-4 list-disc pl-5">
        <li>To create, manage and support user accounts to provide access to our services.</li>

        <li>communication</li>

        <li>To process orders, transactions or payments and provide support and services.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Legal Basis -->
    <section id="legal-basis" class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">
        Legal basis for information collection and processing
      </h2>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        We collect and process your information for only valid legal reasons with your consent,
        which you can withdraw at any time. We may collect and process your information for the
        following reasons
      </p>
      <ul class="mb-4 list-disc pl-5">
        <li>
          You have given us consent to collect and process your information for the purposes of
          providing you with our services, improving our services, communicating with you, security
          and compliance and law enforcement.
        </li>
        <li>
          The processing of your information is necessary for the performance of a contract to which
          you are a party, such as the terms of service or other agreements we have with you.
        </li>
        <li>
          The processing of your information is necessary to comply with a legal obligation, a court
          order or to exercise and defend legal claims.
        </li>
        <li>
          The processing of your information is necessary to protect your vital interests or of
          another person.
        </li>
        <li>
          The processing of your information is related to a task that is carried out in the public
          interest or in the exercise of official authority vested in us.
        </li>
        <li>
          The processing of your information is necessary for the purposes of the legitimate
          interests pursued by us or by a third party are not outweighed by your interests or
          fundamental rights. For example, we may process your information to
          <ul class="mb-4 list-disc pl-5">
            <li>
              We may use your information to protect our services, to enforce our terms and
              conditions, to comply with our legal obligations and to protect the rights and safety
              of others.
            </li>

            <li>fraudPrevention</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Third Party Sharing -->
    <section id="section-third-party-sharing" class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">Information sharing and disclosure</h2>

      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        We may share your information with third party vendors, service providers, contractors or
        agents who perform services for us or on our behalf and require access to such information
        to do that work.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4 text-base">Third parties we may disclose your information with include</p>
      <ul class="mb-4 list-disc pl-5">
        <li>Hosting (Supabase, Railway)</li>

        <li>Payment processing (Stripe)</li>

        <li>Authentication (Supabase)</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        During financing, acquisition or bankruptcy proceedings, your information may be shared with
        potential or actual acquirers or investors and their agents.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Web Tracking -->

    <section id="section-web-tracking" class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">Web tracking and cookies</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        We may use various web tracking technologies to collect information about you and your
        activity across our website.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        We may use cookies to collect information about you and your activity across our website.
        Cookies are small data files stored on your device that help us improve our services and
        your experience.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        We may use web beacons, tracking pixels, and other tracking technologies on our website to
        help customize our website and improve your experience.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        We may use third party analytics providers to measure and evaluate access to and traffic on
        our website, create user navigation reports or marketing reports.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Cookie Consent -->

    <section id="section-cookie-consent" class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">Cookie Policy and Consent</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to collect and use personal information
        about you. Our use of cookies is governed by your consent preferences.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        Cookies are small text files that are placed on your device when you visit our website. They
        help us provide you with a better experience by remembering your preferences, analyzing site
        usage, and assisting with our marketing efforts.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        When you first visit our website, you will be presented with a cookie consent banner that
        allows you to accept or reject non-essential cookies. You can change your preferences at any
        time.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        We use Custom in-app preferences to manage cookie consent on our website.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        You can manage your cookie preferences at any time by clicking on the cookie settings link
        in the footer of our website or by adjusting your browser settings.
      </p>
      <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">
        Essential cookies are necessary for the website to function and cannot be switched off. They
        are usually only set in response to actions made by you which amount to a request for
        services.
      </h3>
      <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">
        Analytics cookies allow us to count visits and traffic sources so we can measure and improve
        the performance of our site.
      </h3>
      <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">
        Marketing cookies may be set through our site by our advertising partners. They may be used
        to build a profile of your interests and show you relevant adverts on other sites.
      </h3>
    </section>

    <!-- Security Measures -->

    <section id="section-security" class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">How we protect your information</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        We follow industry best practices to protect your information and implement security
        measures to maintain the safety of your personal information.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Browser Extension -->

    <!-- Data Retention -->
    <section id="section-data-retention" class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">Data retention</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        We retain your information for as long as necessary to provide you with our services, to
        comply with our legal obligations, to resolve disputes, to enforce our agreements or to
        protect our legal interests.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        Your data will be kept for a period of Until account deletion or 7 years for legal records
        after account closure.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        Your data at the end of the retention period will be deleted or anonymized where possible,
        or if this is not possible, then securely stored and isolated from any further processing
        until deletion is possible.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Data Breach Notification -->

    <section id="section-data-breach" class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">Data Breach Notification</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        We take data security seriously and have implemented measures to protect your personal
        information. In the unlikely event of a data breach that affects your personal information,
        we will notify you in accordance with applicable law.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        If we discover a data breach that is likely to result in a risk to your rights and freedoms,
        we will notify you without undue delay.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        We will notify affected users within 72 hours of becoming aware of a qualifying data breach,
        as required by applicable law.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        Our notification will describe the nature of the breach, the types of data affected, the
        likely consequences, and the measures we have taken or propose to take to address the
        breach.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        If you believe your data may have been compromised, please contact us immediately at <a
          href="mailto:scott@rothcollc.com"
          class="text-blue-500 hover:underline">scott@rothcollc.com</a
        >.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Cross-Border Data Transfers -->

    <!-- US State Privacy Laws -->

    <section id="section-us-state-privacy-laws" class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">US State Privacy Laws</h2>

      <!-- California -->
      <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">California Online Privacy Protection Act (CalOPPA)</h3>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        CalOPPA requires commercial websites and online services to post a privacy policy. The
        law&#39;s reach stretches well beyond California to require a person or company in the
        United States (and conceivably the world) that operates websites collecting personally
        identifiable information from California consumers to post a conspicuous privacy policy on
        its website stating exactly the information being collected and those individuals with whom
        it is being shared, and to comply with this policy. See more information about CalOPPA
        compliance at consumercal.org.
      </p>
      <ul class="mb-4 list-disc pl-5">
        <li>
          California residents have the right to know what personal information we collect,
          disclose, and sell about them. To exercise this right, California residents may submit a
          request to us at <a
            href="mailto:scott@rothcollc.com"
            class="text-blue-500 hover:underline">scott@rothcollc.com</a
          >.
        </li>
        <li>
          California residents have the right to request the deletion of their personal information.
          To exercise this right, California residents may submit a request to us at <a
            href="mailto:scott@rothcollc.com"
            class="text-blue-500 hover:underline">scott@rothcollc.com</a
          >.
        </li>
        <li>
          California residents have the right to opt out of the sale of their personal information.
          To exercise this right, California residents may submit a request to us at <a
            href="mailto:scott@rothcollc.com"
            class="text-blue-500 hover:underline">scott@rothcollc.com</a
          >.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Do Not Track signals</h3>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">We do not respond to Do Not Track signals.</p>
      <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">
        Your California Privacy Rights (California&#39;s Shine the Light law)
      </h3>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        California residents have the right to request information about the personal information we
        have shared with third parties for their direct marketing purposes, including the categories
        of information and the names and addresses of those businesses. You can request this
        information once per calendar year. To make such a request, please contact us at <a
          href="mailto:scott@rothcollc.com"
          class="text-blue-500 hover:underline">scott@rothcollc.com</a
        >.
      </p>
      <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">
        California Privacy Rights for Minor Users (California Business and Professions Code Section
        22581)
      </h3>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        California residents under 18 years of age may request the removal of any information that
        they posted to our website. To request removal of such information, please contact us at <a
          href="mailto:scott@rothcollc.com"
          class="text-blue-500 hover:underline">scott@rothcollc.com</a
        >. Note that the removal of such information does not ensure complete or comprehensive
        removal of the content or information posted on our website.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- CPRA (California Privacy Rights Act) -->

    <!-- VCDPA (Virginia Consumer Data Protection Act) -->

    <!-- COPPA (Children's Privacy) -->

    <!-- Privacy Rights -->
    <section id="section-privacy-rights" class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">Your privacy rights</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        You have the right to access, update or delete your personal information. You can also
        object to the processing of your personal information, ask us to restrict processing of your
        personal information or request portability of your personal information.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        You can access, update or delete your personal information by contacting us at <a
          href="mailto:scott@rothcollc.com"
          class="text-blue-500 hover:underline">scott@rothcollc.com</a
        >.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        You can object to the processing of your personal information, ask us to restrict processing
        of your personal information or request portability of your personal information by
        contacting us at <a href="mailto:scott@rothcollc.com" class="text-blue-500 hover:underline"
          >scott@rothcollc.com</a
        >.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Privacy Policy Changes -->
    <section id="section-privacy-policy-changes" class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">Changes to our privacy policy</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        We may update this privacy policy from time to time. The updated version will be indicated
        by an updated &#34;Revised&#34; date and the updated version will be effective as soon as it
        is accessible. If we make material changes to this privacy policy, we may notify you either
        by prominently posting a notice of such changes or by directly sending you a notification.
        We encourage you to review this privacy policy frequently to be informed of how we are
        protecting your information.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Contact -->
    <section id="section-contact" class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">Contact us</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">
        If you have questions or comments about this privacy policy, you can contact us at <a
          href="mailto:scott@rothcollc.com"
          class="text-blue-500 hover:underline">scott@rothcollc.com</a
        >.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base">Rothco Built, LLC</p>

      <p class="mb-4 text-base">123 Main St</p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
